# Canvas App Locator Conventions

The app renders ENTIRELY inside `iframe[name="fullscreen-app-host"]`. Every locator MUST
go through the frame first. NEVER write locators directly on the page for Canvas elements.

```ts
const appFrame = page.frameLocator('iframe[name="fullscreen-app-host"]');
await expect.soft(appFrame.getByRole('button', { name: 'Dashboard' })).toBeVisible();
```

## General rules

- Controls are ABSOLUTELY-POSITIONED SIBLINGS — do NOT scope by a label's parent.
- After open, WAIT for real data (e.g. a row or `/\d+\s*Total\s*Tasks/`) before asserting
  late controls (dropdowns, pagination).
- Match ACTUAL app text, including typos (`Quater to Date` / `Last Quater`).
- Prefer `getByRole` / `getByText` / `getByPlaceholder`. NEVER CSS/appmagic IDs.
- `getByLabel` does NOT work — use placeholder or text.
- NEVER hardcode counts — use regex (`/\d+\s*Drafts/`).
- `expect.soft` for structure; hard `expect` for interaction/navigation.
- NEVER `waitForTimeout` except inside `getDashboardTaskCount`. No `networkidle`.

## Control patterns by screen

**Invoice Overview / Dashboard filters**

- Period / Region often expose as `getByRole('button', { name })` → options via
  `getByRole('option', { name })`. Selected value becomes the button name.
- Unselected Region may show button name `.` (unique on screen).
- Overview My/All may appear as radiogroup — verify empirically; do not assume.

**Create Invoice**

- Mode radios: prefer `getByText('Brand New')` / `getByText('Start with last invoice')`
  (Canvas often has no reliable `radio` role here).
- Toggles: click label text (`Adhoc Invoice`, `Send Instantly`); assert nearby `Yes`/`No`.
- Partner / Project / Product: open via placeholder text (`Find Partner`, `Find Project`,
  `Find items`) — not `getByRole('button', { name: /Find Partner/ })`.
- Options after open: `getByRole('option', { name })`.
- Delete row: `getByRole('img', { name: /delete/i })`, not button.
- Dates often visible as `/\d{1,2}\/\d{1,2}\/\d{4}/`.
- Standard actions (`Close`, `Save Draft`, `Submit`): `getByRole('button', { name })`.
- Rich text: contenteditable — `.fill()` then `toHaveValue()`.

When unsure, measure with MCP (`count()` / evaluate) before swapping strategies.

## Authentication

Auth via `storageState` in `playwright.config.ts`. NEVER add login code.
`auth.json` and `auth/` must NEVER be committed.

## Live MCP exploration (planner / generator)

- Do NOT `browser_wait_for({ text: "Dashboard" })` — iframe text is invisible at top level.
- After navigate: `browser_wait_for({ time: 10 })` then `browser_snapshot` (iframe refs `f1e*`).
- Refs go stale on re-render — re-snapshot before clicking if "not found".
